# PRD: Security & Correctness Audit Fixes

## Objective
Fix 923 identified issues across 5 categories (correctness, security, data integrity, concurrency, config) to achieve 100% production-ready status.

## Current State
- 373 correctness issues (array bounds, null checks, closures, promises)
- 79 security issues (cookies, XSS, CORS, headers)
- 154 data integrity issues (soft-delete filters, timezone handling, unscoped deletes)
- 195 concurrency issues (transactions, race windows, unbounded queues, dedup)
- 122 config/init issues (env mutation, circular requires, override order)

## Fix Phases (Dependency Ordered)

### PHASE 1: CRITICAL SECURITY FIXES (15 Set-Cookie + 61 innerHTML)
**Blocks:** Everything (security)
**Blocked by:** None
**Status:** pending

[1.1] Fix Set-Cookie headers - Add Secure flag to all 15 instances
- Files: src/app/api/auth/google/callback/route.js, src/app/api/auth/login/route.js, src/app/api/auth/logout/route.js, src/app/api/auth/mwr-bridge/route.js, src/lib/next-polyfills.js
- Pattern: Add `; Secure; HttpOnly; SameSite=Lax` to all Set-Cookie values
- Validation: No Set-Cookie without Secure flag

[1.2] Fix unsafe innerHTML - Replace 61 instances with safe alternatives
- Files: src/ui/auth-pages.js, src/ui/checklist-renderer.js, src/ui/client-renderer.js, src/ui/collaboration-dialogs.js, src/ui/common-handlers.js, src/ui/engagement-detail-panels.js, src/ui/engagement-dialogs.js, src/ui/file-dialogs.js, src/ui/global-tags.js, src/ui/layout.js, src/ui/misc-dialogs.js, src/ui/monitoring-dashboard-client.js, src/ui/password-reset-page.js, src/ui/pdf-viewer-renderer.js, src/ui/picker-dialogs.js, src/ui/review-dialogs.js, src/ui/standalone-login.js, src/ui/tender-dialogs.js, src/ui/validation-ui.js, src/ui/virtual-scroll.js, src/ui/widgets.js
- Strategy: Use textContent for plain text, create safe HTML builders for structured content
- Validation: No innerHTML= assignments remain

### PHASE 2: CRITICAL CORRECTNESS FIXES (13 unhandled promises)
**Blocks:** Phase 3+ (prevents runtime crashes)
**Blocked by:** Phase 1
**Status:** pending

[2.1] Fix promise chains - Add .catch() to all 13 unhandled promise chains
- Files: src/lib/query-engine-optimized.js, src/lib/query-engine.js, src/ui/*.js
- Pattern: Every .then() must have matching .catch()
- Validation: All promise chains have error handlers

### PHASE 3: DATA INTEGRITY FIXES (25 soft-delete + 103 timezone)
**Blocks:** Phase 4+ (prevents data loss)
**Blocked by:** Phase 1
**Status:** pending

[3.1] Add deleted_at filters - 25 SELECT queries missing soft-delete filter
- Files: src/app/api/friday/client/*.js, src/app/api/friday/engagement/*.js, src/app/api/friday/rfi/*.js
- Pattern: Add `AND deleted_at IS NULL` to all SELECT WHERE clauses
- Validation: Count softdeleted vs active, verify filters work

[3.2] Fix timezone handling - 103 instances using local timezone instead of UTC
- Files: src/app/api/email/receive/route.js, src/app/api/friday/engagement/stage-counts/route.js, src/app/api/friday/rfi/*.js
- Pattern: Always use `new Date().toISOString()` instead of `Math.floor(new Date().getTime() / 1000)`
- Validation: All timestamps end with 'Z', consistent UTC across all tables

### PHASE 4: CONCURRENCY FIXES (52 transactions + dedup)
**Blocks:** Phase 5+ (prevents race conditions)
**Blocked by:** Phase 3
**Status:** pending

[4.1] Wrap multi-step DB ops in transactions - 52 instances
- Files: src/app/api/auth/*.js, src/app/api/[entity]/*.js, src/app/api/friday/*.js
- Pattern: BEGIN TRANSACTION; [operations]; COMMIT; or rollback on error
- Validation: No check-then-act without atomic update

[4.2] Add idempotency & dedup - 41 notification instances
- Pattern: Use idempotency keys or processed flags
- Validation: No duplicate notifications

### PHASE 5: ROBUSTNESS FIXES (null/bounds/NaN checks + limits)
**Blocks:** Phase 6 (prevents runtime errors)
**Blocked by:** Phase 4
**Status:** pending

[5.1] Add null checks - 50 instances accessing obj.prop without null check
- Pattern: Use optional chaining (?.) or explicit null checks
- Validation: No null dereference errors in logs

[5.2] Add array bounds checks - 251 instances
- Pattern: Use safe accessors (arr[i] || default) or length checks
- Validation: No array out of bounds errors

[5.3] Add NaN/Infinity validation - 26 instances
- Pattern: Validate all arithmetic: isNaN(x), isFinite(x), etc.
- Validation: No NaN/Infinity in outputs

[5.4] Add size limits - 88 instances without upload/buffer limits
- Pattern: Check size before processing, add MAX_SIZE constants
- Validation: Uploads reject > 100MB, buffers capped

### PHASE 6: CONFIG/INIT FIXES (env mutation, circular requires)
**Blocks:** Production deployment
**Blocked by:** Phase 5
**Status:** pending

[6.1] Fix env mutation - Remove all process.env.x = y assignments
- Files: src/lib/*.js, src/config/*.js
- Pattern: Use const + defaults, never mutate process.env
- Validation: No env mutations in hot-reload

[6.2] Fix circular requires - 6 instances
- Pattern: Extract shared code to separate module, import separately
- Validation: Import graph is acyclic

[6.3] Fix config override order - 22 instances with undefined priority
- Pattern: Use consistent pattern: ENV || CONFIG || DEFAULT
- Validation: All env vars override config file

### PHASE 7: VERIFICATION & TESTING
**Blocks:** None (final validation)
**Blocked by:** Phase 6
**Status:** pending

[7.1] Run full test suite - Execute all code paths
- Tests: Login/auth, RFI operations, engagement transitions, file uploads, PDF generation
- Validation: Zero errors in console, all APIs respond correctly

[7.2] Verify with real data - Run migration Phase 3.5
- Validation: 8/8 validators pass, no data corruption

[7.3] Performance check - Run under load
- Validation: p95 latency < 500ms @ 100 concurrent requests

## Success Criteria (ALL MUST PASS)

- [ ] No Set-Cookie without Secure flag
- [ ] No unsafe innerHTML (0/61)
- [ ] All promise chains have .catch() handlers
- [ ] All SELECT queries filter soft-deleted records
- [ ] All timestamps UTC with Z suffix
- [ ] All multi-step DB ops in transactions
- [ ] No null dereference errors
- [ ] All array accesses bounds-checked
- [ ] No NaN/Infinity in outputs
- [ ] All uploads have size limits
- [ ] No env mutations
- [ ] Import graph is acyclic
- [ ] Config override order consistent
- [ ] 8/8 validators pass
- [ ] Zero production errors observed

## Estimate
- Phase 1: 2 hours (regex + find/replace)
- Phase 2: 1 hour (add .catch handlers)
- Phase 3: 2 hours (soft-delete + timezone)
- Phase 4: 2 hours (transactions + dedup)
- Phase 5: 3 hours (null/bounds/limits)
- Phase 6: 2 hours (env/circular/override)
- Phase 7: 2 hours (testing + verification)
**Total: ~14 hours**

## Notes
- All changes execute in plugin:gm:dev with real data
- No mocks/stubs/test files
- All changes committed to git before each phase
- Git reset available if phase fails
- Focus on highest-impact issues first
